<subSubSection pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="61.[699,1228,193,1448]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">ETYMOLOGY: The trivial name is a Latin noun meaning roof. I refer to the moderate convexity of the elytra.</paragraph>
